          "body": "Peter grounds servant-ethics in Christology by quoting and alluding to Isaiah 53 throughout 2:22-25. Christ is the *hupogrammos* (2:21) — the writing-master's traced sample that the pupil copies letter by letter. The believer's life is meant to retrace the lines of the suffering Servant: no sin (2:22), no deceit, no retaliation when reviled, no threats when suffering, and entrustment to *Him who judges righteously* (2:23). Vindication is real; it is just deferred — and it belongs to God, not the sufferer."
